Maintainer: Charles Joly Beauparlant <charles.joly-beauparlant@crchul.ulaval.ca>
Description: This package produces metagene plots to compare the behavior of
    DNA-interacting proteins at selected groups of genes/features.
    Pre-calculated features (such as transcription start sites of protein
    coding gene or enhancer) are available. Bam files are used to increase the
    resolution. Multiple combination of group of features and or group of bam
    files can be compared in a single analysis. Bootstraping analysis is used
    to compare the groups and locate regions with statistically different
    enrichment profiles.
biocViews: ChIPSeq, Genetics, MultipleComparison
